# Playwright Test Patterns

## Core Principles

### 1. Test Data Isolation with Namespaced Data
- **ALWAYS** use unique, randomly generated namespaces for test data
- Each test must create its own data and clean up only its own data
- Never assume a clean database state
- Use `await GenerateUniqueTestNamespaceAsync()` for unique prefixes

```csharp
private string _testNamespace = await GenerateUniqueTestNamespaceAsync();
private string _adminUserName = $"Admin_{DateTime.UtcNow:yyyyMMdd_HHmmss}_{new Random().Next(1000, 9999)}";
```

### 2. Proper Test Data Cleanup
- **NEVER** put cleanup in `DisposeAsync()` - it runs after each test method
- **ALWAYS** call cleanup at the end of each individual test method that creates data
- Use `await CleanupTestNamespaceAsync(_testNamespace);` at the end of each test

```csharp
[Fact]
public async Task Admin_CanCreateNewViolationType()
{
    // Test implementation...
    
    // ALWAYS cleanup at the end of the test method
    await CleanupTestNamespaceAsync(_testNamespace);
}
```

### 3. Reliable Page Loading Strategy
- Use `LoadState.DOMContentLoaded` instead of `LoadState.NetworkIdle` for faster, more reliable waiting
- Add small fixed delays after DOM content loaded to allow Blazor to render
- Wait for specific elements rather than generic page loads

```csharp
private async Task WaitForPageToLoadAsync()
{
    await _page.WaitForLoadStateAsync(LoadState.DOMContentLoaded);
    await _page.WaitForTimeoutAsync(100); // Allow Blazor to render
}

private async Task WaitForViolationTypesPageToLoadAsync()
{
    await WaitForPageToLoadAsync();
    await _page.WaitForSelectorAsync("#page-loading-canary", new PageWaitForSelectorOptions { State = WaitForSelectorState.Detached });
}
```

### 4. Dialog Handling
- **ALWAYS** set up dialog handlers BEFORE clicking buttons that trigger dialogs
- Use `_page.Dialog += ...` before `ClickAsync()` for delete operations

```csharp
// Set up dialog handler BEFORE clicking
_page.Dialog += async dialog => await dialog.AcceptAsync();
await _page.ClickAsync("button:has-text('Delete')");
```

### 5. Data Visibility After Navigation
- After page navigation, use `await _page.ReloadAsync()` to ensure fresh data
- Wait for specific data to appear after reload to confirm Blazor re-fetched data

```csharp
await _page.ClickAsync("text=Violation Types");
await _page.ReloadAsync(); // Ensure fresh data
await _page.WaitForSelectorAsync("text=" + violationTypeName); // Wait for specific data
```

### 6. Blazor Component Error Handling
- Ensure Blazor components handle exceptions gracefully
- Components should set empty collections on error to hide loading canaries
- Prevent infinite loading states

```csharp
catch (Exception ex)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Error loading violation types: {ex.Message}");
    violationTypes = new List<ViolationType>(); // Hide canary on error
}
```

### 7. CI Environment Configuration
- Use `PLAYWRIGHT_HEADLESS=true` environment variable for CI
- Ensure consistent database credentials across local and CI
- Use `ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Test` for test-specific settings

### 8. Comprehensive Debugging
- Add timestamp logging for performance analysis
- Log page content and URLs for debugging
- Use detailed error messages for troubleshooting

```csharp
var startTime = DateTime.UtcNow;
await _page.ClickAsync("text=Violation Types");
var endTime = DateTime.UtcNow;
Console.WriteLine($"[TIMING] Navigation took: {(endTime - startTime).TotalMilliseconds}ms");
```

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

### ❌ Don't Do This:
- Put cleanup in `DisposeAsync()` method
- Use `LoadState.NetworkIdle` for waiting (too slow in CI)
- Set up dialog handlers after clicking buttons
- Assume clean database state
- Use non-namespaced test data
- Skip page reloads after navigation

### ✅ Do This:
- Clean up at the end of each test method
- Use `LoadState.DOMContentLoaded` + small timeout
- Set up dialog handlers before clicking
- Always use namespaced data
- Reload pages after navigation
- Wait for specific elements to appear

## Test Structure Template

```csharp
public class ExamplePlaywrightTests : TestBase, IAsyncLifetime
{
    private IBrowser _browser;
    private IPage _page;
    private string _testNamespace;

    public async Task InitializeAsync()
    {
        _testNamespace = await GenerateUniqueTestNamespaceAsync();
        // Browser setup...
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task Test_ShouldDoSomething()
    {
        // 1. Create test data with namespace
        var testData = await CreateTestDataAsync(_testNamespace);
        
        // 2. Navigate and wait properly
        await _page.ClickAsync("text=Some Link");
        await WaitForPageToLoadAsync();
        
        // 3. Set up dialog handlers BEFORE clicking
        _page.Dialog += async dialog => await dialog.AcceptAsync();
        
        // 4. Perform actions
        await _page.ClickAsync("button:has-text('Delete')");
        
        // 5. Verify results
        Assert.True(await _page.IsVisibleAsync("text=Success"));
        
        // 6. ALWAYS cleanup at the end
        await CleanupTestNamespaceAsync(_testNamespace);
    }

    public async Task DisposeAsync()
    {
        // Only dispose browser resources, NOT test data
        await _browser?.DisposeAsync();
    }
}
```

