## Performance Optimization

- Use `LoadState.DOMContentLoaded` instead of `NetworkIdle`
- Add small fixed timeouts (100ms) instead of waiting for network idle
- Use specific element selectors instead of generic page loads
- Minimize page reloads, but use them when data visibility is critical

## Debugging Checklist

When tests fail:
1. ✅ Check if test data is properly namespaced
2. ✅ Verify cleanup is at the end of test method, not in DisposeAsync
3. ✅ Ensure dialog handlers are set up before clicking
4. ✅ Confirm page loading strategy uses DOMContentLoaded
5. ✅ Check if page reload is needed after navigation
6. ✅ Verify Blazor component error handling
7. ✅ Check CI environment variables and credentials

